rd looking As the financial expert, you will assist in review and recommend remediation/ mitigation plans to the Regional Controller and Regional CFO for follow up with Regional Management Board, internal audit and global controllership. You will also monitor and communicate status of all corporate function processes and controls, developing risk mitigation plans as require. On top of that, you will also facilitate Regional risk assessment process related to financial statement assertions, processes and controls. Working with Shared Services You will be working with SSC to optimise finance processes across the region as well as manage the Operational relationship with SSC for the Region, attending Regional Performance Boards. You will also corporately manage SSC from a Regional perspective and ensure \u2018two sided\u2019 KPIs are being measured, monitored and performance issues are address. This includes providing guidance, support and mentoring to Regional and Local Controllership functions. Successful Applicant You hold an Accounting or Finance degree or equivalent with 15 years of experience in finance roles, including more than half in diverse senior positions managing reporting, financial planning functions, and business support. It would be great if you have prior experience working in Big 4, MNC and/or dynamic, fast-paced and matrix environment, preferably in service industry. You possess a good understanding of US GAAP/IFRS and management accounting practices of a MNC and is able to appreciate and harness technology in finance processes. ",
